154
00:09:29,889 --> 00:09:33,029
It's not even boiling water, it's just lukewarm, that's all.

155
00:09:34,850 --> 00:09:36,929
That means you were putting on an act just now.

156
00:09:36,929 --> 00:09:40,029
If I didn't make it look severe, could I have gotten off work early?

157
00:09:40,029 --> 00:09:42,649
I'm sorry for making you lose an important client.

158
00:09:42,649 --> 00:09:44,369
Client?

159
00:09:44,369 --> 00:09:48,189
He's not a client. He's my second uncle.

160
00:09:48,189 --> 00:09:51,809
As expected from Fu Zeyi. You even lost your temper with your uncle.

161
00:09:51,809 --> 00:09:54,829
In any case, you did well.

162
00:10:07,550 --> 00:10:09,929
How about this? Take the day off tomorrow.

163
00:10:09,929 --> 00:10:11,572
Really?

164
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:40,359
Where do you think you're running off to?

165
00:10:40,359 --> 00:10:43,779
I'm not. Can't I go on a short getaway on my day off?

166
00:10:43,779 --> 00:10:45,879
I happen to be free, too. Let's go together.

167
00:10:45,879 --> 00:10:48,610
I'm used to going on a holiday alone.

168
00:10:48,610 --> 00:10:49,890
Bye bye.

169
00:10:49,899 --> 00:10:54,961
I'm sorry. From today on, you need to get used to traveling with another person.

170
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:18,919
